      The trade-offs: slightly fewer visa-free countries than St. Kitts (145 vs. 157), no US visa-free access (need Grenada for E-2 treaty), and slower processing (3-4 months vs. 45 days). If US access isn't critical and budget matters, Dominica delivers excellent passport utility per dollar invested.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Healthcare on the island is very limited—Princess Margaret Hospital handles basics but serious conditions require evacuation to Martinique or Miami. However, most CBI citizens never reside in Dominica; they hold the passport for travel freedom while living elsewhere with proper healthcare access.
